
1. Compile the server giving the command ->    gcc server.c -o server

2. Open a terminal and compile the client ->   gcc client.c -o client

3. Run Server on one terminal, give a port number as command line argument ->   ./server 9989
	the server will give its IP address.
4. Open one or more terminal and run client on them, give the same port number and the IP address as arguments -> ./client 0.0.0.0 9989

5. Prompt will ask you for the file to be read, type the name of file.The server will find it, if found it will send it